------How to install kafka on Intellij----------------
1. Download jdk 1.8 in your system
2. Install intellij community version in your desktop
3. Open Intellij
	New Project->Choose maven ->project SDK: java 1.8
	Next
	Write Group_Id, Artifact_Id
	project name
	Next
4. Go to pom.xml file
	add dependencies
	Go to google, search for kafka maven repository
	Copy the dependecy from Kafka Client repository
	Paste it on intellij -> Enable import 
5. Download slf4j logger
   Search slf4j simple
   Copy and paste in pom.xml
   Remove the scope test, since we want this dependecy for whole code
